      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOY BLUE NZ (12) is progressing strongly having won his two starts so far this time in. Overcame a wide draw to win here last week, racing deep early before working to the front and going on to salute by more than 8m. Just needs even luck from the back row and he could be hard to stop again. Former Kiwi BEETASTIC NZ (1) has made a good start in WA, winning here fresh and placing in both outings since. Came from this barrier when only 1.7m off the winner last week. Right in this. IM MASSIMO (4) did a good job to come from the widest barrier for a resuming win. Draws lower and is two from two when second-up so could take the next step. LUVBITE (8) may need some luck from a wide draw but is hard to knock off back-to-back wins here.",
